<p id="notice"></p>

<div class="alert-message block-message warning">
  <p>
    A project has a name, and an owner. It has many tasks, and many people as well.
    For sake of the example, we assume people only work on one project. While owners can have many projects.
    A project can have many tags. You can link an existing tag, or add a new tag and link to that.
  </p>
</div>

<table>
  <tr>
    <td>Name</td>
    <td><%= @project.name %></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Owned by</td>
    <td><%= (@project.owner ? @project.owner.try(:name) : 'no owner yet') %></td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h3>Tasks</h3>

<p>
  List all the tasks here
</p>

<table>
  <% @project.tasks.each do |task| %>
    <tr>
      <td><%= task.name %></td>
      <td><%= task.description %></td>
      <td><%= task.done %></td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<h3>Contributors</h3>

<table>
  <% @project.contributors.each do |contributor| %>
    <tr>
      <td><%= contributor.name %></td>
      <td><%= contributor.role %></td>
      <td><%= contributor.description %></td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<h3>Tags</h3>

<table>
  <% @project.tags.each do |tag| %>
    <tr>
      <td><%= tag.name %></td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<%= link_to 'Edit', edit_project_path(@project) %>
<%= '|' %>
<%= link_to 'Back', projects_path %>